Biography

2019-20 (Freshman)

Parham appeared in 30 games during her freshman campaign, collecting 48 points, 86 rebounds and 19 assists for the Bluejays.

Mykel made her Creighton debut in the Bluejays’ 67-54 win at Nebraska-Omaha on Nov. 5 with six points and five rebounds.

Parham collected four points and five boards at Drake on Nov. 16th.

Mykel recorded a pair of blocks and a pair of rebounds against North Dakota State on Nov. 18.

Parham grabbed seven points and 11 rebounds in the Bluejays’ 69-59 win over Temple in the second game of the Cancun Challenge on Nov. 29.

Mykel posted seven points and eight rebounds in Creighton’s 72-62 win over Marquette on Jan. 3.

Parham snagged seven rebounds and blocked a pair of shots in a career-high 23 minutes of action against Butler on Jan. 26.

Apple Valley High School

A four-year letter-winner for the Eagles, Mykel was a two-time All-South Suburban Conference selection.

A two-time MVP for Apple Valley HS, Parham went on to claim the Apple Valley HS 2018-19 Athena Award, given to the school’s top student-athlete.

Parham played club basketball for the North Tartan AAU squad during her final two seasons at Apple Valley HS.

As a senior she delivered 150 blocks and 251 rebounds, earning All State Honorable Mention.

During her junior campaign she averaged double-digit boards (12.0 rpg), collecting 222 rebounds to finish in the top-10 in Minnesota.

Parham also collected 111 blocked shots, the second-most in the state.

In addition to her excellence on the court, Parham was involved with track and field as an Eagle, earning a combined 10 letters at Apple Valley HS.

Off the court, Mykel served as President of AVHS National Honor Society, and was a founding member of the Black Student Union.

Parham was named Academic All-State and captain of the Eagles four times.
